name: Inkanyamba
shortLoreBlurb: Inkanyamba is a creature from Zulu associated with storm serpent, waterfalls. Serpents mark thresholds and hidden wisdom. Linked to tempests and the rule of kings. Appeased for safe passage and rains.
overlapsLinks: Fafnir (Norse), Indra (Vedic), Jörmungandr (Norse), Manannán (Celtic), Naga (India/SE Asia), Perun (Slavic), Poseidon (Greek), Quetzalcoatl (Aztec), Tangaroa (Polynesia), Thor (Norse), Yemaya (Yoruba), Zeus (Greek)
